article.linkText: Dingle scores 19 to carry Penn past Cornell 73-68
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- — Jordan Dingle scored 19 points and Max Martz scored 16 points and Penn earned its fourth consecutive win beating Cornell 73-68 on Saturday night. Andrew Laczkowski scored 10 points and Jelani Williams had six rebounds for Penn (10-12, 7-2 Ivy League). Chris Manon had 20 points, Dean Noll added 19 points and three blocks and Kobe Dickson grabbed seven rebounds for the Big Red (12-7, 4-4). Jordan Jones, the Big Red's leading scorer entering the contest at 11 points per game, scored three points on 1-for-6 shooting. Penn also beat defeated Cornell 79-65 on Jan. 7. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
